-- PROGRAMME AND SATELLITE EVENTS --

The detailed programme can be found on the conference web site:

http://coalg.org/mfps-calco2017/schedule.html

*Special sessions*

MFPS will host four special sessions, each with an invited tutorial speaker.

* Algebraic Automata Theory
Invited tutorial by Laure Daviaud - University of Warsaw, Poland.
* Foundations of Network Programming (special session in honour of Dexter Kozen???s 65th Birthday)
Invited tutorial by Nate Foster - Cornell University, United States.
* Advances in Concurrent Program Verification
Invited tutorial by Derek Dreyer - MPI-SWS, Germany.
* Metrics and Privacy (joint MPFS & CALCO Special Session)
Invited tutorial by Ben Worrell - Oxford, United Kingdom.

*CALCO Workshops*

CALCO 2017 will run together with the workshops CALCO Early Ideas and CALCO Tools, with
dedicated sessions at the end of each conference day.

Additional information on CALCO Early Ideas is available at
http://coalg.org/mfps-calco2017/cfp-early-ideas-workshop.html.

Additional information on CALCO Tools is available at
http://coalg.org/mfps-calco2017/cfp-tools-workshop.html.


